content:
Getting things done! I love a productive day.
*I had the floorboards replaced in my dining  room. You would think we're a herd of elephants given how destroyed the wood was!
*I planted my spring garden. Can't wait for these pretty things to grow in the sun. 
*I walked 50 blocks w my friend, then she sweetly treated me to a lobster roll. I could get used to this!
*I grilled steaks for the fam while my little one made the sides: roasted asparagus, rice, Korean sauce. Mmmm!  
Whew, I will sleep soundly tonight. Dontcha think?

"How do men act on a sinking ship? Do they hold each other? Do they pass around the whisky? Do they cry?"
Sebastian Junger, The Perfect Storm: A True Story of Men Against the Sea

No, they save their iPhones! 

To my 17 year old:
Happy Birthday to my middle child. My happy boy. My gorgeous Big Boy who looks more like a man than a child each day. My hard working, smart, passionate, ambitious, sloppy, silly, always smiling Son.
We wish you all God's blessings. We love you!

"Be sure to fear the Lord and serve Him faithfully with all your heart; consider what great things He has done for you."
1 Samuel 12:24
